cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.MM

This paper deals with the problem of object transfiguration in images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of generative networks and attention mechanisms, which are also relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The attention network predicts spatial attention maps, which can be considered as a form of image segmentation (cs.GR). Finally, the paper presents experimental results that involve the generation of images, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM).
